	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64373856">I think your math is off.

If we assume pre-industrial levels of CO2 at 280 ppm, we've increased to 420 ppm.  So, around 100 ppm.  So, we have an increase of 420 ppm - 280 ppm = 140 ppm.  If we are to increase from 280 ppm to 1000 pm, that would be 720 ppm increase, of which we have increased 140 ppm.

So, we are about 140/720 = 0.19 (or 19%) of the way to 1000 pmm of human increase in the CO2 level.  So, 1/5 of the way there, not 1/3.</div>
	</div>

